# Authentication Bug Fix - Implementation Guide

## Quick Reference: Root Cause Summary

**The Bug:** User logs in successfully but is immediately redirected back to login page.

**Root Causes (in order of impact):**

1. **Race Condition on Hydration (PRIMARY)**
   - AuthGuard checks localStorage before Zustand store hydrates
   - Store appears empty during hydration
   - AuthGuard redirects to login before store loads tokens
   - Result: Infinite redirect loop

2. **Dual Token Storage Format (SECONDARY)**
   - Login page saves tokens in 2 different formats
   - API client only reads from one format
   - Mismatch causes token to be undefined
   - Result: API requests fail with 401

3. **No Token Refresh Mechanism (TERTIARY)**
   - Access token expires after 15 minutes
   - No automatic refresh attempt
   - Expired token causes 401
   - Result: User forced to login again

4. **No Session Validation (QUATERNARY)**
   - Backend session can be invalidated
   - Frontend doesn't check backend session status
   - Frontend thinks user is logged in when they're not
   - Result: API requests fail with 401

---

## Phase 1: Fix Token Storage & Retrieval

### Task 1.1: Unify Token Storage Format

**File:** `/apps/web/src/app/(auth)/login/page.tsx`

**Current Code (BROKEN):**
```typescript
if (data.success) {
  // Save to zustand store (persisted as audira-auth in localStorage)
  const authData = {
    state: {
      user: data.data.user,
      tenant: data.data.tenant,
      accessToken: data.data.accessToken,
      refreshToken: data.data.refreshToken,
      isAuthenticated: true,
    },
    version: 0,
  };
  localStorage.setItem("audira-auth", JSON.stringify(authData));

  // Also save session for backward compat (WRONG - creates mismatch)
  localStorage.setItem("audira-session", JSON.stringify({
    user: data.data.user,
    tenant: data.data.tenant,
    accessToken: data.data.accessToken,
    refreshToken: data.data.refreshToken,
    role: data.data.role,
    loggedInAt: new Date().toISOString(),
  }));

  router.push("/dashboard");
}
```

**Fixed Code:**
```typescript
"use client";

import { useState } from "react";
import Link from "next/link";
import { useRouter } from "next/navigation";
import { motion } from "framer-motion";
import { useAuthStore } from "@/stores/auth-store";

export default function LoginPage() {
  const [email, setEmail] = useState("admin@audira.ai");
  const [password, setPassword] = useState("audira2024");
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);
  const [error, setError] = useState("");
  const router = useRouter();
  const setAuth = useAuthStore((state) => state.setAuth);

  const handleSubmit = async (e: React.FormEvent) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    setLoading(true);
    setError("");

    try {
      const res = await fetch("http://localhost:3378/api/v1/auth/login", {
        method: "POST",
        headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
        body: JSON.stringify({ email, password }),
      });

      const data = await res.json();

      if (data.success) {
        // Use Zustand store to save tokens (single source of truth)
        // This automatically persists to localStorage via persist middleware
        setAuth({
          user: data.data.user,
          tenant: data.data.tenant,
          accessToken: data.data.accessToken,
          refreshToken: data.data.refreshToken,
        });

        // Redirect to dashboard
        // AuthGuard will wait for hydration before rendering
        router.push("/dashboard");
      } else {
        setError(data.error || "Login failed");
        setLoading(false);
      }
    } catch (err) {
      // Fallback: demo login tanpa backend
      if (email === "admin@audira.ai" && password === "audira2024") {
        setAuth({
          user: { id: "demo", name: "Audira Team", email: "admin@audira.ai", role: "ADMIN" },
          tenant: { id: "demo-tenant", name: "Audira Demo", slug: "audira-demo" },
          accessToken: "demo-token-" + Date.now(),
          refreshToken: "demo-refresh-" + Date.now(),
        });
        router.push("/dashboard");
      } else {
        setError("Invalid credentials. Use demo account.");
        setLoading(false);
      }
    }
  };

  // ... rest of component remains the same
}
```

**Key Changes:**
- ✅ Import `useAuthStore` from Zustand
- ✅ Call `setAuth()` instead of manual localStorage.setItem
- ✅ Remove dual storage (audira-session)
- ✅ Add error state for better UX
- ✅ Zustand persist middleware handles localStorage automatically

**Why This Works:**
- Single source of truth: Zustand store
- Automatic persistence: persist middleware writes to localStorage
- Correct format: Zustand handles the `{ state: {...}, version: 0 }` format
- No race condition: Store is ready when needed

---

### Task 1.2: Fix API Client Token Retrieval

**File:** `/apps/web/src/lib/api.ts`

**Current Code (BROKEN):**
```typescript
private getToken(): string | null {
  if (typeof window === "undefined") return null;
  const stored = localStorage.getItem("audira-auth");
  if (!stored) return null;
  try {
    const parsed = JSON.parse(stored);
    return parsed.state?.accessToken || null;  // May be undefined during hydration
  } catch {
    return null;
  }
}
```

**Fixed Code:**
```typescript
import { useAuthStore } from "@/stores/auth-store";

const API_URL = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL || "http://localhost:3378/api/v1";

interface RequestOptions {
  method?: string;
  body?: unknown;
  headers?: Record<string, string>;
}

class ApiClient {
  private baseUrl: string;

  constructor(baseUrl: string) {
    this.baseUrl = baseUrl;
  }

  private getToken(): string | null {
    if (typeof window === "undefined") return null;

    // Primary: Get token from Zustand store (in-memory, always up-to-date)
    const token = useAuthStore.getState().accessToken;
    if (token) return token;

    // Fallback: Try localStorage for backward compatibility during migration
    try {
      const stored = localStorage.getItem("audira-auth");
      if (!stored) return null;
      const parsed = JSON.parse(stored);
      return parsed.state?.accessToken || null;
    } catch {
      return null;
    }
  }

  private async handleUnauthorized() {
    if (typeof window !== "undefined") {
      // Clear auth state
      useAuthStore.getState().logout();
      // Redirect to login
      window.location.href = "/login";
    }
  }

  private async refreshAccessToken(): Promise<boolean> {
    try {
      const refreshToken = useAuthStore.getState().refreshToken;
      if (!refreshToken) {
        await this.handleUnauthorized();
        return false;
      }

      const response = await fetch(`${this.baseUrl}/auth/refresh`, {
        method: "POST",
        headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
        body: JSON.stringify({ refreshToken }),
      });

      if (!response.ok) {
        await this.handleUnauthorized();
        return false;
      }

      const data = await response.json();
      if (data.success && data.data) {
        // Update store with new tokens
        const state = useAuthStore.getState();
        useAuthStore.setState({
          accessToken: data.data.accessToken,
          refreshToken: data.data.refreshToken,
        });
        return true;
      }

      await this.handleUnauthorized();
      return false;
    } catch (error) {
      console.error("Token refresh failed:", error);
      await this.handleUnauthorized();
      return false;
    }
  }

  async request<T>(endpoint: string, options: RequestOptions = {}): Promise<T> {
    const { method = "GET", body, headers = {} } = options;
    const token = this.getToken();

    const config: RequestInit = {
      method,
      headers: {
        "Content-Type": "application/json",
        ...(token ? { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` } : {}),
        ...headers,
      },
    };

    if (body && method !== "GET") {
      config.body = JSON.stringify(body);
    }

    try {
      let response = await fetch(`${this.baseUrl}${endpoint}`, config);

      // Handle 401: attempt token refresh
      if (response.status === 401) {
        const refreshed = await this.refreshAccessToken();
        if (refreshed) {
          // Retry request with new token
          const newToken = this.getToken();
          config.headers = {
            ...config.headers,
            Authorization: `Bearer ${newToken}`,
          };
          response = await fetch(`${this.baseUrl}${endpoint}`, config);
        } else {
          throw new Error("Session expired. Please login again.");
        }
      }

      if (!response.ok) {
        const error = await response.json().catch(() => ({ error: "Request failed" }));
        throw new Error(error.error || `HTTP ${response.status}`);
      }

      return response.json();
    } catch (err: any) {
      if (err.message === "Failed to fetch" || err.name === "TypeError") {
        throw new Error("Cannot connect to server. Make sure the API is running.");
      }
      throw err;
    }
  }

  get<T>(endpoint: string) {
    return this.request<T>(endpoint);
  }

  post<T>(endpoint: string, body?: unknown) {
    return this.request<T>(endpoint, { method: "POST", body });
  }

  patch<T>(endpoint: string, body?: unknown) {
    return this.request<T>(endpoint, { method: "PATCH", body });
  }

  delete<T>(endpoint: string) {
    return this.request<T>(endpoint, { method: "DELETE" });
  }
}

export const api = new ApiClient(API_URL);
```

**Key Changes:**
- ✅ Get token from Zustand store first (in-memory, always current)
- ✅ Fallback to localStorage for backward compatibility
- ✅ Add `refreshAccessToken()` method
- ✅ Detect 401 and attempt refresh before failing
- ✅ Retry original request with new token
- ✅ Handle refresh failure gracefully

**Why This Works:**
- Token always current: Zustand store is in-memory
- Automatic refresh: 401 triggers refresh attempt
- No infinite loops: Refresh failure redirects to login
- Backward compatible: Falls back to localStorage if needed

---

### Task 1.3: Fix AuthGuard Hydration

**File:** `/apps/web/src/components/layout/auth-guard.tsx`

**Current Code (BROKEN):**
```typescript
